President Joe Biden has announced several key nominees for positions in the Department of Health and Human Services, Department of Education, and Department of Veterans Affairs. Chiquita Brooks-LaSure is nominated to be the Administrator for the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS). She has extensive experience in health policy and played a crucial role in implementing the Affordable Care Act. James Kvaal is nominated to be the Under Secretary of Education. He has worked on initiatives to make college more affordable and increase graduation rates. Richard Sauber is nominated to be the General Counsel for the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs. He is a skilled litigator with experience in fraud cases and has served as general counsel for Freedom House. These nominees will help advance President Biden's agenda and work towards a stronger and more inclusive nation.